          <li>Hoarders:</li>
          <ol>
            <li>Reality show:  Probably the most "real-feeling" of the reality shows as opposed to a more scripted style like "Kitchen Nightmares".
                There's no doubt that drama is enhanced by editing and the introduction of certain family and friends.</li>
            <li>Invasion of privacy:  A combination of seeing a car-wreck moments after it happened with turning that crazy person on your block's life inside out by seeing the secrets they have in their home.</li>  
            <li>Shock value:  No matter how many times you see it, you are still shocked by the disgusting mess AND by the craziness.</li>
            <li>See the crazy:  The most unique part of this show is just how visual the mental illness is.  The mess is a mirror to the mind of the owner and it's fascinating, disturbing and very personal.</li>
